          <h1>Will I actually become fluent?</h1>
          <p>Yes, you will to the point of being able to converse over a broad range of everyday topics. However, this is on the condition that that you fully complete all the online exercises as to our guidance given and participate fully in the live Zoom sessions. We also teach you all the tips and tricks of how to learn Chinese independently to help you to expedite your progress and to help you with your learning beyond the course.</p>
          <h1>Will I learn how to write in Chinese?</h1>
          <p>For the sake of the bootcamp and its limited timeframe, the focus is on how to converse in the language orally. Most Chinese natives rarely write and mostly type, hence the ability to learn to write in Chinese will be developed through typing the language on a computer - this will be taught during the course. If there are learners who wish to practice/learn writing by hand, additional resources will be provided.</p>
          <h1>What if I don't want to speak?</h1>
          <p>We of course won't force you, though to be fluent in a foreign language, speaking is an essential part of the process. Though you may worry about making a mistake, making mistakes is part of the learning process in order to learn and you will be very much supported by your teachers and peers in a relaxed and positive environment! If you are unwilling to speak in the language at all, then this language learning course may not be for you.</p><br>
